Defendant Daniel A Peace in court with attorney Gary E. Rosenthal.  Defendant Daniel A Peace in custody.  Sara B. Lewis appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for sentencing hearing. State is prepared to proceed. Defendant made oral pro se motion to have a new attorney for sentencing. Court held colloquy with the defendant. Discussion regarding defendant's letter to the court. Court denied defendant's request for new counsel. Attorney Rosenthal requested to withdraw from this case on his own motion, which the court denied for reasons stated on the record. Based on defense counsel's statements about preparation for the sentencing, Court inquired of the defendant if he wished for a short adjournment which the defendant denied on the record. 
Sentencing proceeded. Statements made as to sentencing. Additional statements by Lisa S. 

As to COUNT 1-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 20 YEARS, consecutive to sentence in case 05CF1125, consecutive to COUNT 2 with credit for 0 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 10 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 10 YEARS.  

As to COUNT 2-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 20 YEARS, consecutive to sentence in case 05CF1125, consecutive to COUNT 1 with credit for 0 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 10 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 10 YEARS.  

Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Earned Release Program. The defendant is not appropriate for the Substance Abuse Program.

Court costs, fees and restitution be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
1) Restitution set at ZERO;
2) Register and comply with the sex offender registry;
3) Comply with all rules as set forth by agent;
4) Maintain absolute sobriety;
5) No contact with the victims or any witnesses in the trial;
